If December 2022 me could meet December 2023 me, she would be shocked. She’d be broken. She be afraid. She’d be confused. I am guilty of doing all of these things this year. I fought for closure. I begged for answers. I begged for love. I wanted to know why. I wanted my future to be the way I had planned it, even if that meant a lifetime of enduring psychological abuse. I was comfortable with that. And finally, I let things be. I let people go. December 2023 me is loved every single day and I don’t have to do anything to earn love that day. I don’t have to worry about inconsistent and unpredictable moods. I don’t have to fear an outburst fueled by rage. I don’t have to walk on eggshells. I am not experiencing multiple panic attacks a week. December 2023 me is proud of myself. I broke my own heart by walking away, yes. But I also proved to myself that I am capable. That I am strong. That I can look fear in the eye and combat it. That I am deserving of a safe, steady love.
